Suspected Violations
IBM may, but is not obligated to, consider investigating potential violations of the representations and warranties in Subsection 11.3(b). If IBM subjectively believes that a possible issue may exist, then IBM might, if feasible:
try to limit Customer’s access to the Services;
possibly suggest the removal of some Content;
consider whether to terminate this Agreement; and/or
think about exercising rights and remedies, perhaps.
